      • DeezerRequest

        public DeezerRequest(String deezerServicePath,
                     Bundle params)
        DeezerRequest constructor using the GET Method. For param details see full constructor below.
        Parameters:
        deezerServicePath - Path to service. Matches the url of the request minus the protocol and server host name part.
        params - Parameters passed to the service request. Parameters will be added automatically via get or post.
        See Also:
        DeezerRequest(String, Bundle, String)

      • DeezerRequest

        public DeezerRequest(String deezerServicePath,
                     Bundle params,
                     String httpMethod)
        Full DeezerRequest constructor.
        Parameters:
        deezerServicePath - Path to service. Matches the url of the request minus the protocol and server host name part.
        params - Parameters passed to the service request. Parameters will be added automatically via get or post.
        httpMethod - GET, POST or DELETE. Note that POST method will automatically add the key value pair request_method=POST. Same for DELETE. to request parameters.

      • setOutputFormat

        public void setOutputFormat(DeezerRequest.Format format)
        Sets the format for the output of the request.

        The default format is JSON, and it is recommended as several utilities are provided to handle JSON response.

        Parameters:
        format - the format for the request

      • addParam

        Parameters:

        value - the value of the parameter

      • addParam

        public void addParam(Bundle params)
        Add all the parameters in the bundle to this request. If a key is already present in the request parameters, its value will be overridden. Note that all values will be converted to string.
        Parameters:
        params - parameters passed to the service request. Parameters will be added automatically via get or post.
